      comments: "Everyone plays their role well and is an integral part in moving this story forward"
    }
    rating: "Very Good"
  }
  story {
    writer {
      name: "Bong Joon-ho"
    }
    rating: "Incredible"
    comments: "The concept is very metaphorical as the title is about how these working class family tries to be a parasite and influtrate this upper class family, giving commentary on class dynamics in doing so; the plot structure is well laid out as the movie is broken up into two parts, to make it a 'black comedy-thriller'; the character writing is incredible as this dynamic between the rich and the poor family shows the contrast between the two lifestyles and how smug the upper class is to the lower class"
  }
  screenplay {
    writer {
      name: "Bong Joon-ho"
    }
    writer {
      name: "Han Jin-won"
    }
    rating: "Incredible"
    comments: "The dialogue is profound, sharp, and well written; the humor is good as it helps make this movie feel like a black comedy in the first half; the symbolism is incredible profound as the whole movie is commentary on class dynamics and the seperation between the rich and the poor in Korea; the foreshadowing is very evident and helps give clues for what is going to happen, and this was very evident on a second watch"
  }
